Consider the following recursive Java method. What will be the output when the method is called as `y(6, 6)`?

```java
public static void y(int n, int z) {
    if (n >= 10) {
        System.out.println(n);
        System.out.println(z);
        return;
    } else {
        System.out.println("z=" + z);
        n = n + 2;
        y(n, z + 2);
        y(z + 5, 4);
        System.out.println(n + 1);
        return;
    }
}
```

